## 1. Purpose

This policy maps the **Australian Cyber Security Centre (ACSC) Essential Eight** mitigation strategies to AI-specific risks at {{ business_name }}. As AI tools introduce new attack surfaces — including prompt injection, model poisoning, data exfiltration via AI outputs, and shadow AI usage — the Essential Eight framework must be extended to address these risks. This policy aligns with **AI6 Guidance for AI Adoption** (Practice 5: Secure AI systems) and the **ACSC Essential Eight Maturity Model** (July 2024).

---

## 2. Scope

This policy applies to:

- All AI tools, platforms, and APIs used or hosted by {{ business_name }}
- AI libraries, SDKs, and dependencies used in software development
- AI plugins and extensions within productivity software
- AI model configurations, training data, and prompt libraries
- Infrastructure supporting AI workloads (servers, endpoints, cloud environments)

