## 3. Essential Eight — AI-Specific Implementation

### 3.1 Control 1: Application Control (Whitelisting Approved AI Tools)

**Standard objective:** Prevent execution of unapproved or malicious programs.

**AI-specific risks:** Staff installing unapproved AI applications; unauthorised AI browser extensions capturing data; shadow AI tools bypassing security review.

**AI-specific controls:**

| Control | Implementation |
|---------|---------------|
| AI tool whitelist | Maintain a register of approved AI tools; block installation of unapproved tools via endpoint management |
| Browser extension control | Block unapproved AI browser extensions (e.g., ChatGPT wrappers, AI writing assistants) via group policy |
| API gateway controls | Route all AI API calls through a managed gateway; block direct calls to unapproved AI endpoints |
| Mobile device management | Prevent installation of unapproved AI apps on corporate mobile devices |
| Shadow AI detection | Monitor network traffic for connections to known AI service domains not on the whitelist |

{% if shadow_ai_controls %}
{{ business_name }} has shadow AI controls in place. Integrate the AI tool whitelist with existing shadow AI detection mechanisms.
{% else %}
**Recommendation:** Implement shadow AI detection as a priority. Monitor DNS queries and outbound connections to known AI service endpoints (e.g., api.openai.com, generativelanguage.googleapis.com, anthropic.com).
{% endif %}

