## 4. Maturity Assessment Checklist

Assess {{ business_name }}'s maturity for each Essential Eight control as applied to AI systems. Use the ACSC maturity levels:

- **Level 0** — Not implemented
- **Level 1** — Partly aligned with the intent of the mitigation strategy
- **Level 2** — Mostly aligned with the intent of the mitigation strategy
- **Level 3** — Fully aligned with the intent of the mitigation strategy

| # | Control | Current Level | Target Level | Gap | Owner |
|---|---------|--------------|-------------|-----|-------|
| 1 | Application control (AI tool whitelisting) | | | | |
| 2 | Patch applications (ML libraries, AI SDKs) | | | | |
| 3 | Configure macros (AI plugins/add-ins) | | | | |
| 4 | User application hardening (prompt injection) | | | | |
| 5 | Restrict admin privileges (AI platform access) | | | | |
| 6 | Patch operating systems (AI servers/endpoints) | | | | |
| 7 | Multi-factor authentication (AI platforms) | | | | |
| 8 | Regular backups (AI configs, data, prompts) | | | | |

### Maturity Target Recommendations

| Data Classification | Minimum Target Maturity |
|--------------------|------------------------|
| Public / Internal data only | Level 1 |
| Confidential data | Level 2 |
| Restricted data or automated decisions | Level 3 |

